// 🔷 1. Git & GitHub Workflow
// Git is a version control system used to track changes in code and collaborate with others using platforms like GitHub.

// 📌 Initial Setup
// Initialize repository:

// git init
// Create a repository on GitHub and copy its URL

// Link local project to GitHub:

// git remote add origin <repo-url>
// Add files:

// git add .
// Commit changes:

// git commit -m "Your message"
// Push to GitHub:

// git push -u origin main
// 🔁 Daily Workflow
// After initial setup, use:

// git add .
// git commit -m "message"
// git push
